Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. From the `admin.php` routes file, I can see that:

```php
Route::resource('comments', CommentController::class)->only(['index', 'edit', 'update', 'destroy']);
```

This confirms that the DELETE endpoint `/admin/comments/{comment}` is mapped to the `destroy` method in `CommentController`. 

Based on my analysis of the `destroy` method in the controller:
1. It takes a `Comment $comment` parameter (route model binding)
2. It deletes the comment with `$comment->delete()`
3. It returns a `RedirectResponse` redirecting to the comments index route with a success message
4. The route name is `admin.comments.destroy` which corresponds to `/admin/comments/{comment}`

The response will be a redirect (HTTP 302) to the admin comments index page (`/admin/comments`) with a success flash message.

